# File: `content/examples/overrides/README.md`

```markdown
# UNCLASSIFIED

# PXE Override Examples

This directory contains example profile and Kickstart template overrides for the AeroLIT PXE content image.

These files are examples only. They are not automatically used by the image unless copied or mounted into the runtime override directory.

Runtime override paths:

```text
/overrides/profiles/
/overrides/templates/
```

## How to use these examples

Copy the example override directory to the system or bundle location that will be mounted into the container as `/overrides`.

Example:

```bash
mkdir -p /opt/aerolit/pxe-overrides
cp -r content/examples/overrides/* /opt/aerolit/pxe-overrides/
```

Run the PXE content image with:

```bash
podman run --rm -d \
  --name pxe-content \
  -p 18080:8080 \
  -e PXE_SERVER=<pxe-server-ip-or-hostname> \
  -e PXE_PORT=18080 \
  -v /path/to/extracted_isos:/iso:Z \
  -v /opt/aerolit/pxe-overrides:/overrides:Z \
  registry.gitlab.us.lmco.com/lit/containers/pxe-content:latest
```

Then check:

```text
http://<pxe-server>:18080/generated/status.txt
http://<pxe-server>:18080/generated/status.json
http://<pxe-server>:18080/boot.ipxe
```

## Important rules

Use `/overrides/profiles/` to change profile behavior.

Use `/overrides/templates/` to change Kickstart rendering.

Do not treat `/ks` as the normal customization path. `/ks` is generated output. Manual edits under `/ks` are supported for emergency use only and are controlled by `PXE_GENERATED_KS_EDIT_POLICY`.

# UNCLASSIFIED
```

