# File: `content/examples/overrides/profiles/10-minimal-custom-title.yml`

This is a safe example that replaces the built-in `minimal` profile with a customized menu title while still using the normal minimal Kickstart template.

```yaml
profile_id: minimal
title: Minimal Installs - Site Default
install_label: Minimal
menu_target: minimal
implemented: true
show_in_main_menu: true
uefi: true
bios: true
supported_os:
  - rhel10
  - rhel9
  - rhel8
  - rhel7
kickstart_template: ks/{{ os_id }}-minimal.ks.j2
kernel_args:
  - inst.text
  - nomodeset
```

Expected result:

```text
Minimal Installs - Site Default
```

appears in `boot.ipxe` instead of the built-in minimal title.

