# File: `content/examples/overrides/profiles/20-developer-workstation-example.yml`

This example turns the developer workstation placeholder into an implemented profile for RHEL 8 only.

It is intentionally scoped to RHEL 8 so users understand how `supported_os` limits profile generation.

```yaml
profile_id: developer_workstation
title: Developer Workstation Installs
install_label: Developer Workstation
menu_target: developer_workstation
implemented: true
show_in_main_menu: true
uefi: true
bios: true
supported_os:
  - rhel8
kickstart_template: ks/rhel8-developer-workstation.ks.j2
kernel_args:
  - inst.text
  - nomodeset
```

Expected result:

```text
Install RHEL 8 Developer Workstation (UEFI)
Install RHEL 8 Developer Workstation (BIOS / Legacy)
```

appear as real boot targets in `boot.ipxe` when `rhel8iso` is detected.

