# File: `content/examples/overrides/templates/ks/rhel8-developer-workstation.ks.j2`

This is a simple example Kickstart template for the developer workstation profile.

It reuses the built-in partials where possible and adds a small package section.

```jinja
# Example Developer Workstation Kickstart override
#version=RHEL{{ os_major }}

{% include "partials/install-mode-text.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/language-keyboard.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/timezone.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/network-dhcp.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/root-password.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/repo-url.ks.j2" %}

zerombr
clearpart --all --initlabel
autopart --type=lvm

%packages
@^minimal-environment
vim-enhanced
git
curl
tar
python3
%end

{% include "partials/services-basic.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/kdump-enabled.ks.j2" %}
{% include "partials/post-empty.ks.j2" %}
```

Notes:

- Keep include paths quoted.
- Keep template paths relative.
- Do not include `inst.ks`, `inst.repo`, `inst.stage2`, `ip`, or `initrd` in profile `kernel_args`; the generator owns those values.
- Add real site packages only after confirming the repositories contain them.

