## Optional example: emergency `/ks` edit workflow

This is not a source-controlled example file. It is an operational workflow.

Use this only when you need to quickly test or repair generated Kickstart output on a running PXE server.

```bash
# edit the generated file directly in the running web root
vi /etc/nginx/html/ks/rhel8-minimal.ks
```

With the default policy:

```text
PXE_GENERATED_KS_EDIT_POLICY=preserve
```

manual edits are preserved. The regenerated candidate file is written under:

```text
/generated/preserved-kickstarts/
```

To force the generator to overwrite manual `/ks` edits:

```text
PXE_GENERATED_KS_EDIT_POLICY=overwrite
```

Recommended rule:

```text
Use /overrides for planned customization.
Use /ks manual edits only for emergency troubleshooting.
```

